The government is urging South Africans in strife-torn Ukraine to try and leave for neighbouring countries as Russia continues to bomb Ukrainian cities and towns. Some South Africans there say it has been difficult to board trains. Student Vuvu Ntonga speaks about her experience. Courtesy #DStv403 #eNCA  JOHANNESBURG - The government is urging South Africans in strife-torn Ukraine to try and leave for neighbouring countries. Some South Africans there say it has been difficult to board trains. Student Vuvu Ntonga speaks to eNCA.